  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>cashew nuts</strong> to a large baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 6-8 min or until the cashews are lightly toasted, then transfer to a plate and reserve the tray for later</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641811519237-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641811519237-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641811519237-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641811519237-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1641811519237-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim then chop the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> roughly</p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks, keeping the <strong>stems</strong> and <strong>leaves</strong> separate</p><p>Cut the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) then chop into large, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641811523875-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641811523875-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641811523875-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641811523875-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1641811523875-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>beef mince </strong>to a large bowl with the <strong>chopped spring onions</strong>, <strong>diced</strong> <strong>apricots</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>parsley stems</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>harissa paste </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Mix thoroughly with clean hands, then divide the mixture into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> and shape into meatballs</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641811528301-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641811528301-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641811528301-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641811528301-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1641811528301-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to one side of your reserved baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!)</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped red pepper</strong> to the other side of the tray and put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the meatballs are cooked through and the pepper has softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641811532850-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1641811532850-x400.jpg",
